Lesson 4 – Programming (CS) vs Productivity Tools (IT)

Do Now What you'll learn Key Vocabulary Activities Plenary

Do Now

Think back to Lessons 1–3 (CS vs IT, Algorithms vs Workflows, Binary vs Presentation).

Today you’ll compare Programming with Productivity Tools.

Match each statement to Programming (CS) or Productivity (IT):

1. Writes code to automate a task.
Answer: Programming (CS)
2. Uses spreadsheet formulas to total a budget.
Answer: Productivity (IT)
3. Debugs errors using print statements.
Answer: Programming (CS)
4. Formats a report with styles and headings.
Answer: Productivity (IT)

What you'll learn today

By the end of this lesson, you will be able to:

  • Explain what a program is and how we run it.
  • Use basic formulae to work with numbers in a spreadsheet.
  • Say when to use coding vs productivity tools.

How you'll know you've got it

  • Write a tiny program that takes input and gives output.
  • Build a simple spreadsheet with SUM and AVERAGE.
  • Give one example where both are used together.

Key Vocabulary

Program — a set of instructions a computer can run.
IDE — software used to write and run code.
Variable — a named value that can change in a program.
Formula — an instruction in a spreadsheet (e.g., =SUM(A1:A5)).
Function — a reusable piece of code or a spreadsheet command.
Template — a pre‑made layout for quick, consistent work.

Main Activities

CS Track – Tiny Program

  1. Open Python / Replit.
  2. Ask for a name and a score out of 100.
  3. Print a message: “Well done <name>! Grade: A/B/C…”
name = input("Name: ")
score = int(input("Score (0-100): "))
if score >= 80:
    grade = "A"
elif score >= 60:
    grade = "B"
else:
    grade = "C"
print(f"Well done {name}! Grade: {grade}")

IT Track – Budget Sheet

  1. Create a table: Item, Cost (£).
  2. Use =SUM(…) to total the cost; =AVERAGE(…) for the mean.
  3. Add Conditional Formatting to highlight cost > £20.

Compare & Reflect

  • When is it better to code? When is a tool faster?
  • How could you use both together in one project?

Plenary – Hands‑Up Task

  • 🟥 Hands up if you preferred the Programming task.
  • 🟦 Hands up if you preferred the Productivity Tools task.
  • 🟨 Hands up if you liked both.
  • 🟩 Hands up if you’re still unsure.
